obo:RO_0002333  a  owl:ObjectProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_894  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The authors investigated a transgenic mouse line expressing Neurexin 1-alpha with an extracellular HRP tag. Functionality of this transgene was shown by rescue of Neurexin triple KO phenotypes in Zhang et al. J Neurosci. 2005, 25:4330-42. PMID: 15858059\n\nFig. 4 shows that Neurexin 1-alpha labeling was observed mainly in the ER and at presynaptic terminals. Labeling included the presynaptic plasma membrane but was also present at presynaptic vesicular structures.\n\n22/6/2017 Pim\n- The \"intergral component of ...\" part of the selected term was derived from the transmembrane domain(s) of the protein.. Experimental description: transgenic mouse line expressing Neurexin 1-alpha with an internal horseradish peroxidase (HRP) epitope tag" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099056 replaced by GO:0042734" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3670-7863" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0912-1514" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_894" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

